# LLM Rules Format

## Core Structure

```mdc
---
description: ACTION when TRIGGER to OUTCOME
globs: *.mdc
---

# Rule Title

## Context
- When to apply this rule
- Prerequisites or conditions

## Requirements
- Concise, actionable items
- Each requirement must be testable

## Examples
<example>
Good concise example with explanation
</example>

<example type="invalid">
Invalid concise example with explanation
</example>
```

## File Organization

### Location

- Root: `.cursor/rules/`
- Extension: `.mdc`
- Structure: `<category-folder>/<NNN-name>.mdc`

```zsh
.cursor/rules/
├── 000-index.mdc           # Master catalog (root level)
├── 000-foundations/        # Core principles
├── 100-tools/              # Dev environment
├── 200-languages/          # Language rules
├── 300-frameworks/         # Platform rules
├── 400-testing/            # Quality standards
├── 500-operations/         # CI/CD, monitoring
├── 600-documentation/      # Doc standards
├── 700-workflows/          # Process rules
├── 800-project/            # Project-specific
└── 900-meta/               # Templates
```

### Naming Convention (Dewey-style)

Format: `NNN-kebab-name.mdc` where NNN follows Dewey Decimal principles:

```
000-099  Foundations & Core Principles
         000       Index/catalog
         001-009   Architecture patterns
         010-019   Design philosophy
         020-029   Code organization
         
100-199  Development Environment & Tools
         110-119   Linters & formatters
         120-129   Build tools
         130-139   Version control tools
         
200-299  Languages
         210-219   Clojure
         220-229   Python
         230-239   JavaScript/TypeScript
         240-249   Go
         250-259   Rust
         
300-399  Frameworks & Platforms
         310-319   Web frameworks
         320-329   Kubernetes/Containers
         330-339   Cloud platforms (AWS, GCP, Azure)
         340-349   Databases
         
400-499  Testing & Quality
         410-419   Unit testing
         420-429   Integration testing
         430-439   E2E testing
         440-449   Code review
         
500-599  Operations & Infrastructure
         510-519   CI/CD
         520-529   Monitoring & observability
         530-539   Security
         
600-699  Documentation
         610-619   API documentation
